8K</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eazT1aa.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bRNcs8K</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[blank666man]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>“Was my position eliminated or not?”</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/eDEwVSn</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dHUjV0I.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Front page EDIT: Yay! Front Page! I just wanted to add that I’ve never worked in food service but after watching the movie ‘Waiting…’ and more recently the Hulu series ‘Bear’ I have a new found respect for everyone that works in the restaurant industry.

I’ve always known it’s difficult for all restaurant staff but was clueless as to how much work really goes into running a restaurant. Especially through the pandemic. So if you are in that line of work, hats off to you and thanks for all you do!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/eDEwVSn</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[dorenavant]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The ferry I was on caught fire and ran aground. Safely off now!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/twg88Rl</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6fWJoez.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The ferry is from Nova Scotia to PEI in Canada. Dark smoke started billowing up, from the engines supposedly. It smelled like diesel.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gnsdWVa.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We were mustered into the cafeteria while the fire alarm was going off. Power went out.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/B0pNqON.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>You could see smoke spreading out across the water.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O6jxIF1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Soon we were on deck waiting to evacuate.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rJyYbQB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Smoke kept coming, but not quite so much.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rqhQU0w.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some of the crew were pretty good. The guy who kept walking around saying “keep calm!” (not the guy shown) not so much.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wZ2wyy7.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The lowered the inflatable thing to evacuate people. People on shore got in their lobster boats and pleasure craft to come out and help evacuate.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SqyPM2y.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some people were going “wheeee!” as they went down.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QKCOlpf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The inflatable thing was taking on a bit of water - I’d say 2 or 3 inches in the centre. But a lobster boat came alongside fast to pick us up.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/A5VZiAg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>People were generally in good spirits. Old people, kids, pets, etc, all seemed to be gotten off safely and calmly.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hflvrxs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I was not the only one taking pictures.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TzTP6cV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This dog made it off! It doesn’t seem happy though.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6CoGSfk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The unloading of the inflatable thing took a bit of doing. It was a big step up into the lobster boat, and some people needed help.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JfdIBdb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We were soon on our way away.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/uWpjq0P.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The boat doesn’t look happy.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MSo122S.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Certainly the most interesting trip I’ve had in a while.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bnCBk95.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We came off on the dock.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wTJNTbu.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The life vests were soon stacked. I wanted to keep mine.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NgfSxxk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Boats kept coming in from the ship. I think that these might be crew.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WmAXuEd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As I was loaded on to the bus I took a few pictures of a helicopter that flew in. I’m now in the visitors centre waiting to get my name and details taken. There’s a TV here showing a static ad for the ferry: “Travel by sea. Save time. Drive less.” I’m giggling a bit to see it.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/twg88Rl</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mrchalifax]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I dunno who this is, but he's right.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/8QMjI5z</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qFMGraZ.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/8QMjI5z</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[reformedxile]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I smell a lawsuit</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/tALaMQQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bKwZETR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kdYagVF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zT5NiRE.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/08MySnD.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.im